OL,3,CParents fight to get terminally ill
OL,4,Ctoddler the palliative care he needs
OL,6,FThe former bodyguard said the syringes
OL,7,Fare no longer provided by the
OL,8,Fcardiology team the family visits
OL,9,Fevery two weeks, and no one else has
OL,10,Fbeen able to provide them. He added
OL,11,Fthat some of Jaxson's medicine is
OL,12,Fmeasured in 0.2ml, meaning he can't
OL,13,Fuse a measuring cup.
OL,15,FJim said his family was advised to re-
OL,16,Fuse the syringes, sterilising them
OL,17,Fbetween uses, but said the numbers on
OL,18,Fthem are "starting to fade".
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/17
