OL,3,CParents fight to get terminally ill
OL,4,Ctoddler the palliative care he needs
OL,6,FIt found that nearly a half (47%) of
OL,7,Fareas are partially meeting this
OL,8,Fstandard, while one quarter (23%) are
OL,9,Fnot meeting it at all.
OL,11,FThe 24/7 end of life care at home
OL,12,Fstandard is not met at all in Northern
OL,13,FIreland and only in a minority of
OL,14,Fareas in Scotland and Wales.
OL,16,FThe charity said workforce shortages,
OL,17,Finconsistencies in the way support is
OL,18,Fplanned and funded by local NHS and
OL,19,Fcouncil bodies, and an estimated #295m
OL,20,Fchildren's palliative care funding gap
OL,21,Fin England, are to blame.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G8/17
