OL,3,CParents fight to get terminally ill
OL,4,Ctoddler the palliative care he needs
OL,6,FAs a former bodyguard, Jim said he has
OL,7,Fbeen shot at, stabbed, and bottled -
OL,8,Fbut nothing could prepare him for the
OL,9,Fpain of battling for his son's life.
OL,11,F"As a parent you want to protect your
OL,12,Fchild, sometimes I feel helpless and
OL,13,Flike I've put him in a situation I
OL,14,Fcan't get him out of," he said.
OL,16,F"It's the hardest job I have ever had
OL,17,Fin my life. The intensity of caring,
OL,18,Fit's 24/7 ` we always have to watch
OL,19,Fhim. If his stent blocks, it's too
OL,20,Flate. In the day, he is never left
OL,21,Falone. I always have an eye on him.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
