OL,3,CParents fight to get terminally ill
OL,4,Ctoddler the palliative care he needs
OL,6,F"Neither should they have to rely on
OL,7,Fthe generosity of the public to access
OL,8,Fthe care they need, much of which is
OL,9,Fprovided by the voluntary sector.
OL,11,F"We would not accept maternity
OL,12,Fservices relying on donations when a
OL,13,Fchild's life begins, so why do we
OL,14,Faccept this for palliative care when a
OL,15,Fchild's life ends?"
OL,17,FA spokesperson for the Department for
OL,18,FHealth & Social Care provided the
OL,19,Ffollowing statement:
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G14/17
OL,2,W/*%+.!/*%/"-$ /*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,
